{"pr_number": 4293, "pr_title": "fix: log4j properties files", "pr_createdAt": "2020-01-13T12:16:49Z", "pr_url": "https://github.com/confluentinc/ksql/pull/4293", "timeline": [{"oid": "d17830549d33a51128ae0f1e90546b94df45cb7e", "url": "https://github.com/confluentinc/ksql/commit/d17830549d33a51128ae0f1e90546b94df45cb7e", "message": "fix: log4j properties files\n\nThis PR removes the log4j.properties files from our production jars. The presence of such files will make it more tricky for clients to correctly configure log4j with their own properties files as log4j picks the first it finds on the class path by default.\n\nAlso, changed many log levels from `ERROR` to `WARN` as important warnings are being excluded, which could be hiding issues.", "committedDate": "2020-01-13T12:15:05Z", "type": "commit"}, {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDM2NTkxODQ1NA==", "url": "https://github.com/confluentinc/ksql/pull/4293#discussion_r365918454", "bodyText": "can we keep this one at ERROR?  Connect spams the logs with a ton of messages without this one when it loads the plugins. I think that's the only place it's used", "author": "agavra", "createdAt": "2020-01-13T17:03:54Z", "path": "config/log4j.properties", "diffHunk": "@@ -23,13 +24,23 @@ log4j.appender.streams=org.apache.log4j.ConsoleAppender\n log4j.appender.streams.layout=org.apache.log4j.PatternLayout\n log4j.appender.streams.layout.ConversionPattern=[%d] %p %m (%c:%L)%n\n \n-log4j.logger.kafka=ERROR, stdout\n+# loggers\n+\n+log4j.logger.org.reflections=WARN, stdout", "originalCommit": "d17830549d33a51128ae0f1e90546b94df45cb7e", "replyToReviewId": null, "replies": [{"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDM2NTkzMDk0Mg==", "url": "https://github.com/confluentinc/ksql/pull/4293#discussion_r365930942", "bodyText": "Sure.", "author": "big-andy-coates", "createdAt": "2020-01-13T17:30:19Z", "replyToReviewId": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDM2NTkxODQ1NA=="}], "type": "inlineReview"}, {"oid": "c71e0042f2465c